==Scottish Gaelic==
===Noun===
'''muir''' {{m}} and {{f}}, '''mara''' ''[[genitive|gen]]'', '''marannan''' {{p}}.
#The [[sea]] 
# [[sea]], [[ocean]]
#* Lean mi thar muir thu.
#** I followed thee over the sea.
#* air muir 's air tìr
#** by sea and by land
# [[wave]]
# {{p}} large [[billows]]
# {{f}} [[worry]], [[discomposure]], mental suffering
#* Nach ann air a tha a' mhuir an diugh!
#** How troubled he is today!
#* Tha muir ort an diugh, a Dhomhnuill.
#** You are in the [[dolours]] today, Donald.

===Usage notes===
*Feminine in [[w:Badenoch|Badenoch]].
*In [[w:Lewis|Lewis]], the [[nominative]] is feminine and the [[genitive]] is masculine.

